<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (NAVPAK) (1997) - SECTION 3.5: ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEM DIAGNOSTICS,
        ACCELERATOR PEDAL POSITION SENSOR/IVS SWITCH (APS/IVS) - REMOTE ACCELERATOR PEDAL SENSOR - FAULT DETECTION
        MANAGEMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="PROCTYPE" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAULT DETECTION MANAGEMENT</title>
        <para>The ECM monitors the voltage at the RPS terminal for voltage to determine if the signal is in range. A
            minimum voltage level is established to verify that the circuit is not open and a maximum voltage level is
            established to verify that the signal is not shorted to a voltage source. When the ECM detects a voltage out
            of range, the pedal will be disabled and flash code 213 for Out of Range Low or code 214 for Out of Range
            High will be set.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="BOLD">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="f19017100">3.83</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the remote accelerator pedal sensor circuit diagram and
            <emph type="BOLD">Table
                <hotlnk xrefid="f19017101">3.29</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the connector checks.
        </para>
        <figure id="f19017100" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg1248" filename="../figeg1/eg1248.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.83 Remote Accelerator Pedal Sensor Circuit Diagram</caption>
        </figure>
        <table id="t19017189">
            <title>Table 3.29 Remote Accelerator Pedal Sensor Connector Check</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="54p"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="54p"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="180p"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="3" spanname="S1T3"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Remote Pedal Sensor Connector Voltage Checks</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">(Check with Remote Pedal Sensor disconnected and ignition key "ON")
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>A to grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>0v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>A positive voltage reading indicates a short to another circuit</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>B to grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>0v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>A positive voltage reading indicates a short to another circuit</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>C to grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>5 &#177; .5v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Voltage out of specification indicates an open circuit or short to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>(2) to grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>12v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>On/Off switch voltage when switch is in the "ON" position.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>Remote Pedal Sensor Connector Resistance Checks</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>(Check with remote pedal sensor disconnected, ignition key "OFF" and all accessories
                                off.)
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>A to grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>> 1000 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Less than 1000 ohms indicates a short to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>B to grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>> 1000 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Less than 1000 ohms indicates a short to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>C to grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Greater than 5 ohms indicates circuit is open.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>(1) to grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>> 1000 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Less than 1000 ohms indicates a short to ground with switch closed</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Harness Resistance Checks</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Check with breakout box installed on chassis harness only &#38; sensor
                                    connector disconnected.
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>5 to B</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>More than 5 ohms indicates a high resistance or an open circuit</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>6 to C</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>More than 5 ohms indicates a high resistance or an open circuit</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>30 to A</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>More than 5 ohms indicates a high resistance or an open circuit</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>36 to (1)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>More than 5 ohms indicates a high resistance or an open circuit with switch closed.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Operational Voltage Checks</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Check with breakout box installed &#38; RPS sensor connected to
                                    connector .
                                </emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>30 to 6</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>.5 to 4v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Voltage should be low at idle position and should increase by depressing the pedal.
                                Voltage reading should change smoothly and there should be no position that causes a
                                sudden increase or decrease in voltage.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>36 to grd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>12v or 0v</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>On/Off switch voltage: 12v when ON, 0 volts when OFF</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Fault Code Descriptions</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>213 = RPS Signal was less than 0.249 volts. Circuit open or shorted to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S1T3">
                            <para>214 = RPS Signal was more than 3.91 volts. Sensor shorted internally or short to VBAT
                                or VRef.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
